sentences.chinese: 希望大家谅解一下，嘿嘿。

sentences.english: He touched them on the head and went on working.
sentences.chinese: 然后他摸摸他们的头，嘿嘿笑着继续干活儿。

sentences.english: Heck, Apple may even come out with an actual television someday.
sentences.chinese: 嘿嘿，苹果甚至可以自己整个真正的电视出来。

sentences.english: Attention! There is a chubby little hand reaching out for the dessert.
sentences.chinese: 注意照片中一只小胖手儿正朝甜点的方向抓来，嘿嘿。

sentences.english: Heihei, This is the picture of the library with the style of European building.
sentences.chinese: 嘿嘿，这是太原科技大学具有欧式建筑风格的图书馆。

sentences.english: Hmmmmmm, I am going to have a gooooooooooood sleep.
sentences.chinese: 嘿嘿，我可要好好睡上一顿了。

sentences.english: I'm Jingjing, come from the beautiful molonggang , Sichuan province.
sentences.chinese: 嘿嘿，我是晶晶，熊猫来自那美丽的四川卧龙岗。

sentences.english: Running this Sat. ( Dec . 8), for next Sat. 28KM Mountain Running Training !
sentences.chinese: 嘿嘿，大家为下周的28km爬山训练赛做准备啊。

sentences.english: I was planning my next five-minute escape.
sentences.chinese: 嘿嘿，我在计划着接下来五分钟的逃跑。

sentences.english: Idon't think that would be a very permanent thing.
sentences.chinese: 再次，嘿嘿，我不认为这样的事情将会长久。

sentences.english: Otherwise, well, my transcript speaks for itself.
sentences.chinese: 否则，嘿嘿，我的成绩单副本就是证明。

sentences.english: How my English is not good hehe.
sentences.chinese: 我的英文也不怎么好嘿嘿。

sentences.english: Hey Hey, will having never thought this wild countryside open nation also have a beauty?
sentences.chinese: 嘿嘿，没想到这荒郊野外也会有美人？

sentences.english: Hey, this is my student, kaka.
sentences.chinese: 嘿嘿，这可是我的学生噢。

sentences.english: But I know that the girls definitely love smug myself, hey, me too.
sentences.chinese: 不过我知道，女孩子肯定爱臭美喽，嘿嘿，我也是。

definition: to laugh heartily/to burst into loud laughter
interjection indicating approval, appreciation or agreement
(literary) youngster/(old) young fellow (term of address used by the older generation)/(old) I, me (used in speaking to one's elders)
to give a hollow laugh/to force a smile/forced laugh/CL:聲|声[sheng1]
(affectionate form of address for a male who is not very much younger than oneself) my boy/old pal
